MindWave 🌊 invests in building a strong community of dedicated experts with its consultants and clients. We also aim to be the movement of change that provides a better way of working and growing together.

We believe in a more human way of working. We just choose to do it differently! 🚀

Our client portfolio consists of large companies in FinTech, Pharma, Media and many more.




About the role

MindWave is looking for Big Data Software Engineers to join our talented team of engineers!

The position is for a brand new initiative to overhaul the data management processes in an established enterprise in the FinTech industry.




What you'll be doing

As a senior data engineer/developer, you will be part of a dynamic team where you will be working on data flows interacting with various systems using various protocols. As we are building a data management platform as part of the strategy to enable frictionless transaction, you together with our dynamic team of professionals using up-to-date technologies will be delivering data management features and capabilities managing & delivering data across different business practices internally and externally. You will develop the platform that is based on industry best practices, standards and governance framework that are robust, scalable & performant as well as ensuring high data quality and data integrity.




Qualifications

Professional skills

At least 8+ years’ experience in Software development/data engineer practices/consulting;
University bachelor’s or master’s degree in computer science or related engineering discipline;
Strong communication skills (both written and verbal);
Team player, willing to work in a multicultural environment;
Able to lead, coach and groom junior team members.

Technical skills

Proven experience in data engineering and software development practices;
Solid programming/coding experience in Java Development;
Solid understanding of data engineering & ETL Development ;
Having experience in data API and solid understanding of distributed system is a strong advantage;
Having experience with SQL, PL/SQL in Oracle DB;
Hands-on experience on Denodo, Cloudera or any data management platform is a strong advantage;
Hands-on experience with Apache NiFi, Kafka, Spark, Hadoop is a strong advantage;
Hands-on experience with AWS managed services such as Amazon Kinesis, MSK, Redshift, S3 is a plus;
Experience with CICD development & deployment tools such as Maven, Jenkins, Nexus and Git;
Experience with scripting language, primarily Unix Shell, Perl, Python;
Having expertise in manual & automation testing;
Practical working experience in an Agile development (scrum) context;
Proven experience as a key technical resource leading the development of solutions;
Demonstrated ability to influence and consult (providing options with pros, cons and risks) around all key technical decisions during project delivery;
Knows or wants to learn how to translate business problems into software & technical requirements;
Strong interpersonal skills, customer centric attitude, ability to deal with cultural diversity;
Proven team player and team builder;
Demonstrated aptitude for learning new technologies quickly;
Able to thrive in a fast paced, goals and deadlines driven environment;
Passionate about change & improvement and constantly challenging the status quo.




What we offer

Attractive salary package;
Compensation package that includes private medical and life insurance, meal vouchers, mobile and internet plan;
Homeworking as default!
Be part of an awesome group of people 😎




Equal Opportunities

MindWave is an equal opportunity employer. All aspects of employment, including hiring, promotion, remuneration, or discipline, are based solely on performance, competence, conduct, or business needs.

